Did you know Luke Feldman at all?

10:05.072 --> 10:05.513
Very well.

10:06.394 --> 10:06.815
Very well.

10:07.416 --> 10:11.682
Can you give me a couple of quick insights on Luke and David Feldman?

10:11.702 --> 10:15.027
Well, no, I remember him from when I was a kid, from when I was 18, and

10:15.293 --> 10:20.239
We're travelling to London each year with his wife, Big Astrakhan Colin Coat.

10:20.259 --> 10:23.923
I remember him buying the Chaucer at Christie's sale in 1974.

10:25.284 --> 10:30.610
I remember I wasn't there because Bart was sent over for the sale, I think.

10:30.630 --> 10:38.379
But just after I left London, we had a sale of the Library of Siegfried Sassoon.

10:38.399 --> 10:43.765
And apart from one smallish sale in 19...

10:44.555 --> 10:55.913
68 or 67 in London, which was a sale of pamphlets of Swift, where Traylon bought something like 80% of the sale.

10:57.916 --> 11:02.083
I mean, that's like batting 400, you know what I mean?

11:02.103 --> 11:07.111
